    "actions": [
      {
        "startDie": 1,
        "endDie": 2,
        "name": "Fang Strike (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Blood Stalker lunges at a target, attempting to sink its fangs into their flesh. It makes a melee attack, dealing D6 Piercing damage on a hit. If the attack hits, the target must make an Endurance check or take additional D4 Necrotic damage as the Blood Stalker's bite weakens their vitality.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 3,
        "endDie": 3,
        "name": "Blood Frenzy",
        "description": "<div><p>The next time the Blood Stalker reduces a creature to 0 Health or 0 Toughness with a melee attack, it can use a Reaction to make another melee attack against a different target within reach, gaining Advantage on the attack check.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 4,
        "endDie": 6,
        "name": "Vampiric Drain (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Blood Stalker targets a creature, biting into it and dealing D6 Piercing damage. The Blood Stalker gains a boost to Health equal to half the damage dealt. This gain resets after 1 round.</p></div>"
      }
    ],
    "description": "<div><p>Blood Stalkers are terrifying predators that prey upon any living creature to sustain their insatiable thirst for blood. Its pale, alabaster skin is accentuated by crimson eyes that glint with a predatory hunger, almost distracting from the sight of its terrible fangs. The Blood Stalker moves with eerie grace and preternatural speed, allowing it to unleash volleys of furious attacks, gaining power from the blood spilled and even healing itself.</p></div>",
